  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-notaccepted-20260419",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment is not accepted at this time due to two factors assessed marginally below their required levels for a modelRiskLevel-3 COU. (1) Test conditions (achieved: 2, required: 3): All validation testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 loading configuration (50 mm offset, 5 mm/min). The required level 3 demands at least two distinct loading conditions to demonstrate that the model's predictive capability is not narrowly tuned to a single experimental configuration. The single-condition dataset does not provide sufficient evidence of generalizability. (2) Model inputs (achieved: 2, required: 3): Material properties were sourced from the ASTM F136 specification rather than lot-specific coupon data for the 11 validation constructs, and geometric dimensions were taken from nominal CAD rather than CMM measurements of the actual test specimens. Although the specification data is conservative and dimensional tolerances are tight, the required traceability to specimen-specific inputs is not demonstrated. These two shortfalls are related: the same resource constraints that limited testing to a single condition also precluded specimen-specific material characterization. The assessment team determined that no offset rationale is applicable — the shortfalls represent genuine evidence gaps that must be remediated rather than compensated by other evidence. Remediation path: (a) conduct compression-bending validation at a second offset distance (e.g., 40 mm) or loading rate; (b) obtain lot-specific tensile coupon data for at least a subset of the validation constructs and demonstrate that specification-level inputs bound the results. Upon successful remediation, resubmission is expected to achieve the required levels and support an Accepted decision.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
